introduction: This video highlights a virtual conference that took place on February 15th and 22nd, featuring AI product owners, engineers, and product managers. The conference included keynotes from industry experts such as Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, and Dro from Uber. The lineup also included workshops on AI product ownership and engineering. The conference focused on AI product management and the importance of evaluating the outcomes of models in production.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to the Virtual Conference
content: The virtual conference was held on February 15th and 22nd.
It featured keynotes from industry experts in AI product ownership, engineering, and management.
The conference included workshops on AI product ownership and engineering.
The focus of the conference was on AI product management and evaluating outcomes in production.

sections.title: Section 2: Keynote Speakers
content: Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, and Dro from Uber were among the keynote speakers.
They discussed their experiences and insights in AI product ownership, engineering, and management.
Their talks highlighted the importance of evaluating outcomes in production.
Their presentations were well-received by the audience.

sections.title: Section 3: Workshops
content: The conference included workshops on AI product ownership and engineering.
These workshops provided hands-on experience and practical applications of AI in product management.
The workshops focused on evaluating outcomes in production and improving AI models.
The attendees found the workshops informative and valuable.

sections.title: Section 4: Importance of Evaluating Outcomes in Production
content: Evaluating outcomes in production is crucial for the success of AI models.
It helps identify issues and improve model performance.
The conference emphasized the importance of evaluating outcomes in production.
The attendees learned about various methods for evaluating outcomes in production.

sections.title: Section 5: Conclusion and Next Steps
content: The virtual conference was a success and provided valuable insights into AI product ownership, engineering, and management.
The attendees left with a better understanding of the importance of evaluating outcomes in production.
The conference paved the way for future discussions and collaborations in the field of AI product management.
The organizers plan to hold more virtual conferences in the future.
